{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01HoVbwfPg917EEeZrXnLyoB","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Good. The vm.max_map_count is already 262144, so I don't need the sysctl init container. The StorageClass is \"standard\" using rancher.io/local-path provider, which supports ReadWriteOnce PVCs.\n\nThere's also a `curl-test` and `openssl-toolbox` pod already running - I should be careful not to interfere with them.\n\nNow let me write the manifests. Since vm.max_map_count is already set correctly, I can skip the sysctl init container, which simplifies things.\nThe WaitForFirstConsumer binding mode means the PVCs will stay pending until the pods actually get scheduled, which is fine for this setup. Let me create and apply the manifest.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":383,"cache_read_input_tokens":40783,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":383},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"ebcfe451-5bf6-4137-ae12-5e34c5ab3dca","uuid":"5514242a-278d-43e7-b3e5-c07c15ece506","request_id":"req_011CcfDTewFpMSGMxgjJbvkS"}
