{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01P5YTV3VY1BwBFAs6FeX4Q5","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"ES is running and responding! But the cluster is not formed yet (cluster_uuid is `_na_`). That's because es-0 is waiting for es-1 and es-2 to join the cluster (needed for `cluster.initial_master_nodes` = es-0, es-1, es-2). The readiness probe checks `/_cluster/health` which requires the cluster to be formed.\n\nThe issue is:\n1. es-0 is running but can't form the cluster until es-1 and es-2 join\n2. es-1 and es-2 can't start until es-0 is Ready (StatefulSet ordered startup)\n3. es-0 can't be Ready until the cluster is formed (readiness probe)\n\nThis creates a deadlock. I can fix this by using `podManagementPolicy: Parallel` to let all three pods start simultaneously instead of waiting for each one to be Ready, which will let them discover each other and form the cluster. I should also adjust the readiness probe to be less strict during initial startup.\n\nUpdating the StatefulSet...","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":354,"cache_read_input_tokens":46109,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":354},"output_tokens":20,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"ebcfe451-5bf6-4137-ae12-5e34c5ab3dca","uuid":"834c513b-0ce2-47b3-802c-27911e7a7bcc","request_id":"req_011CcfEHtbNi1Vak3iYzcx4N"}
