{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01Rq2nMyyUQZuEGQofcJsR42","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I can't patch the `podManagementPolicy` field after creation. I need to:\n\n1. Delete and recreate the StatefulSet with `podManagementPolicy: Parallel`\n2. The PVCs will remain after the StatefulSet is deleted, so data will persist\n\nLet me update the manifest to add `podManagementPolicy: Parallel` and also fix the readiness probe to be more lenient initially.\n\nActually, the readiness probe issue is separate from the podManagementPolicy. Even with Parallel, all 3 pods will start at the same time, discover each other, form the cluster, and then all 3 readiness probes will pass at around the same time.\nI'll delete the StatefulSet and recreate it with the parallel pod management policy. Since the PVCs are already bound to specific node paths through the local-path provisioner, the new pods will rebind to the same volumes and preserve the data. The readiness probe should work fine once the cluster forms—the health endpoint will return 200 when all nodes are connected. The real issue is the sequential startup caused by the default OrderedReady pod management policy. I could either switch to Parallel startup or simplify the readiness probe to check the root endpoint, which returns 200 before cluster formation—this would let all three nodes come up quickly enough to discover each other and form the cluster.\n\nPatching the readiness probe...\n\nActually, I realize I could simplify this by using a TCP socket check instead, which would pass as soon as Elasticsearch starts listening on port 9200. This would let the first pod become ready much earlier and allow the cluster to bootstrap.\n\nBut thinking it through more carefully, that still doesn't solve the core issue—I need all three pods running and clustered together for reads and writes to work. The real solution is to delete and recreate the StatefulSet with `podManagementPolicy: Parallel`, which will start all pods simultaneously. The PVCs will persist, so I just need to delete the StatefulSet, update the YAML, and recreate it.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":986,"cache_read_input_tokens":46463,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":986},"output_tokens":24,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"ebcfe451-5bf6-4137-ae12-5e34c5ab3dca","uuid":"0abdbc12-2ee9-4646-8ba9-50d1e430beaf","request_id":"req_011CcfEJj89CqMBdsuv3xwTa"}
