{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01KxHHLAYNEK3EViFJZRthRJ","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Everything is working. Here's a summary of what was deployed:\n\n**Resources created in `elasticsearch` namespace:**\n\n| Resource | Name | Notes |\n|---|---|---|\n| ConfigMap | `es-config` | `elasticsearch.yml` — HTTP+transport TLS via `es-http-tls` secret |\n| Service | `es-headless` | ClusterIP None, `publishNotReadyAddresses: true`, used for discovery |\n| Service | `es-http` | ClusterIP, port 9200 HTTPS — the required endpoint |\n| PodDisruptionBudget | `es-pdb` | maxUnavailable: 1 |\n| StatefulSet | `es` | 3 replicas, `podManagementPolicy: Parallel`, 2Gi PVCs |\n\n**Key decisions:**\n- `podManagementPolicy: Parallel` — all 3 pods start simultaneously; without this, es-0 deadlocks waiting for es-1/es-2 to form the quorum needed for its own readiness probe to pass.\n- Same `es-http-tls` certificate reused for transport SSL with `verification_mode: certificate` (validates CA chain, relaxes hostname check) — avoids needing a separate transport cert.\n- `ELASTIC_PASSWORD` injected from the existing `elastic-password` secret; no password bootstrapping needed.\n\n**Final state:** 3-node cluster green, 3/3 nodes, HTTPS reads and writes confirmed through `es-http:9200`."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":435,"cache_read_input_tokens":50781,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":435},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"ebcfe451-5bf6-4137-ae12-5e34c5ab3dca","uuid":"6ba553e5-dda1-43f4-994a-351e6fe82957","request_id":"req_011CcfEV3DMU8qgJPRf7dxwr"}
